All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Block
The block class is an actor that only moves when pushed by the player or sliding over ice.
BoatPath
A boat that moves back and forth, and the player can walk on and off it.
Bug
The Bug class represents a type of monster that navigates a game grid based on specific rules.
Button
Button Class that can be stepped on to disable traps.
ChipsChallengeApplication
Application class for the JavaFX application.
ChipsChallengeController
Controller class for the main view.
ChipSocket
The ChipSocket is a tile that acts like the LockedDoor but deducts a currency of chips from the player's inventory.
Clock
A Clock that displays the remaining time for each level.
ComputerChip
A ComputerChip is a item that can be picked up by the player and used to unlock doors.
Direction
Enum used for handling movement and facing direction.
Dirt
The Dirt class is a tile that becomes a path once the player has walked on it.
Exit
The Exit class is a tile that represents an exit in the game.
ExtraLife
An ExtraLife item can be picked up by the player and gain an extra life.
Frog
The Frog class, a subclass of Actor, represents a type of monster that tries to move in the shortest path to the player's location.
GameManager
The GameManager class is responsible for managing communications between tiles on each layer.
GameManager.DeathState
Enum for handling the different ways the player can die.
GameTimer
A Timer that ticks every entity in the level on a variable interval.
GameViewController
The UI controller for the game view.
HighScoresViewController
The UI controller for the high scores view.
HighScoreTable
Manages high score tables per level and player profiles.
Ice
Ice is a tile that player may walk on.
Ice.IceType
Enum used to determine the type of ice block the actor is moving over.
IncreaseTime
An IncreaseTime item can be picked up by the player and increase the time.
InputManager
The InputManager class allows other classes to create handlers for input events it provides static helper functions for other parts of the program.
Invinc
An Invincible item can be picked up by the player and become Invincible.
Key
The key can be picked up by the player to unlock a door.
Layer<T>
The Layer class handles an individual layer of Tile subclasses.
Level
The level class handles reading and parsing level format data.
LevelDetails
The level details class gets a level's metadata from level-index.txt as well as the duration from the level file.
LevelsViewController
The UI controller for the levels view.
LockedDoor
Class LockedDoor is a door that can be opened with a key.
Path
Path is tile that all actors may walk over.
PathFindDetails
This class stores details for a position for the Frog's pathfinding.
PathFindNode
This class acts as a node in the A* pathfinding algorithm used by the Frog class.
PauseMenu
Pause screen for the level.
PinkBall
The PinkBall class represents a type of monster in the game.
Player
Player is an actor which is controlled by the user and interacts with other tiles and actors in the level.
Player.InventorySlot
The slots that different items take up in the inventory.
PlayerData
Represents a player with a name and score.
PlayerProfile
Represents a player profile that holds information about a player's name and unlocked levels.
PlayerProfileManager
Manages a collection of player profiles including creation, deletion, and retrieval of profiles.
PlayerViewController
The UI controller for the players view.
Speed
A Speed item can be picked up by the player and improve speed.
Tile
The Tile class represents a single tile in a grid-based system, such as a game map.
TileType
The TileType enum represents the possible types of tiles in a grid-based system, such as a game map.
Trap
A Trap, if set, will prevent whatever walks on it from moving.
Wall
Wall is a tile that no actors may walk over.
Water
Water kills the player if walked on, and becomes a path if a block is pushed onto it.
